Spring Core Annotaion
	1. @Component
		It is sterotype class level annoation, which is used to create and register
		beans (java objects)  in the spring IoC container. It marks class as a spring
		manged component which wpring IoC Container automatically detects it during component 
		scanning. for ex :
		
		@Component
		class Employee{
			
		} 

		It is equivalent to Bean tag
		<bean id="emp" class="com.jmd.classes.Emplyee"/>
		
		@Component has multiple specialized annotion such as
			a. @Service - used on the top of service class onlye
			b. @Repository - used on the top of Dao class or repository class and it
			also enables databasae exception translation
			c. @Controller - it used on the top of controller class
			in spring mvc desing pattern only
		
	Above annotion functionality are the same as @component annotaion, but, 
	we use on different classes
	
	2. DependencyInjection Annotiaon
		1. @Autowired - we write in the top of reference variable, it automatically, 
						injects one object reference into another object, spring Ioc
						automatically finds a matching beans and inject it. for example
						
						equivalent to 
						<contructor ref="employeeDao"/>
						
						@Service
						class EmployeeSerice{
						
							@Autowired
							private EmployeeDao ep;
							
						}
						
		2. @Primary - it is class level and method level annoation, it marks a java object
					  as default object when multiple object are present. While injecting one
					  object into another object.object to take
